H0.text: Which western country was the first to extend the right to vote in national elections to women. Australia

H1.text: Which western country was the first to extend the right to vote in national elections to women. United Kingdom

H2.text: Which western country was the first to extend the right to vote in national elections to women. United States

H3.text: Which western country was the first to extend the right to vote in national elections to women. Nz

A4.text: New Zealand became the first nation in the world in which all women had the right to vote in parliamentary elections.

A5.text: The Electoral Bill granting women the franchise was given Royal Assent by Governor Lord Glasgow on 19 September 1893.
